====500 mM NaPi pH 7.4 or 8.0====
{| class="wikitable" border="1"
|-
!  quantity pH7.4
! quantity pH8.0
!  stock solution
|-
| 15.6 g || 4.7 g || NaH2PO4.H2O
|-
| 103.7 g || 124.9 g || Na2HPO4
|-
| colspan="3"| ''q.s.'' to 1 L with water
|-
|}
*Fill a beaker with 800 mL water
*While rapidly stirring:
**Add 15.6g NaH2PO4
**Add 103.7g Na2HPO4
***Add this quantity in small portions otherwise the powder forms a barely soluble clump.
**Adjust the pH to 7.4
*q.s. to 1L
*I have prepared this buffer twice with variations of +/- 0.02g. 
**pH-values were 7.40 and 7.41 and no further adjustment was needed.

