====0.5 M EDTA====
{| class="wikitable" border="1"
|-
!  quantity
!  stock solution
|-
| 186.1 g || disodium ethylenediamine tetraacetate.2H2O
|-
| 18.5 g || NaOH pellets
|-
| colspan="2"| ''q.s.'' to 1 L with water
|-
|}
*Take 800 mL water and stir vigorously
*Weigh 186.1g of disodium ethylenediamine tetraacetate.2H2O and add to the solution
**This will be a white suspension
*Insert pH-meter
*Weigh 18.5g NaOH pellets and add to the suspension; wait until dissolved
*Continuously adjust the pH to 8 by adding drops of a concentrated NaOH-solution
**I usually overshoot the pH to 8.05, because the pH will drop when EDTA dissolves
**Wait until solution is clear
**If needed, adjust to pH 8
*q.s. to 1L
*Optional: Filter over a 0.22um filter


